<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><ordinance xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.xml.gov.hk/schemas/hklm/1.0 https://www.elegislation.gov.hk/schemas/hklm.xsd" xmlns="http://www.xml.gov.hk/schemas/hklm/1.0" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" identifier="/hk/cap655!en" xml:lang="en"><meta><docType>cap</docType><docNumber>655</docNumber><docStatus>In effect</docStatus><docName>Cap. 655</docName><dc:identifier>/hk/cap655!en</dc:identifier><dc:date>2025-05-23</dc:date><dc:subject>legislation</dc:subject><dc:language>en</dc:language><dc:publisher>DoJ</dc:publisher><dc:rights>The Government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region</dc:rights></meta><main><longTitle startPeriod="2025-05-23T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1747878856163_001" name="longTitle" temporalId="longTitle">An Ordinance to prohibit the unauthorized use of the title of, and the unauthorized association by certain other means with, The Chinese Medicine Hospital of Hong Kong; to amend certain provisions in various enactments so that The Chinese Medicine Hospital of Hong Kong is covered by those provisions; and to make a related amendment.</longTitle><commencementNote>[23 May 2025]</commencementNote><enactingFormula>Enacted by the Legislative Council.</enactingFormula><section startPeriod="2025-05-23T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1748244148838_002" name="s1" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><heading>Short title</heading><content>This Ordinance may be cited as The Chinese Medicine Hospital of Hong Kong Ordinance.</content></section><section startPeriod="2025-05-23T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1748244148854_003" name="s2" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Unauthorized use of title of The Chinese Medicine Hospital of Hong Kong etc.</heading><subsection id="ID_1748244148854_004" name="1" temporalId="s2_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><leadIn>For the purposes of this section, a body of persons falls within the specified description if it is a body of persons (whether corporate or unincorporate) that—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1748244148870_005" name="a" temporalId="s2_1_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><leadIn>purports or holds itself out—</leadIn><subparagraph id="ID_1748244148870_006" name="1" temporalId="s2_1_a_1"><num value="1">(i)</num><content>to be The Chinese Medicine Hospital of Hong Kong or any part of it; or</content></subparagraph><subparagraph id="ID_1748244148885_007" name="2" temporalId="s2_1_a_2"><num value="2">(ii)</num><content>to be in any way associated with that hospital;</content></subparagraph></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1748244148885_008" name="b" temporalId="s2_1_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>uses the title “The Chinese Medicine Hospital of Hong Kong” or “香港中醫醫院”; or</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1748244148885_009" name="c" temporalId="s2_1_c"><num value="c">(c)</num><content>uses a title in any language that so closely resembles the title “The Chinese Medicine Hospital of Hong Kong” or “香港中醫醫院” as to be capable of misleading any person into believing that the body of persons is The Chinese Medicine Hospital of Hong Kong or any part of it or is in any way associated with that hospital.</content></paragraph></subsection><subsection id="ID_1748244148901_010" name="2" temporalId="s2_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>A person must not, without the written consent of the Secretary, incorporate or otherwise form a body of persons that falls within the specified description.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1748244148901_011" name="3" temporalId="s2_3"><num value="3">(3)</num><leadIn>A person must not, without the written consent of the Secretary—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1748244148901_012" name="a" temporalId="s2_3_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>hold the office of director or any other office of, be an organizer of, or otherwise work in connection with, a body of persons that falls within the specified description; or</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1748244148916_013" name="b" temporalId="s2_3_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>be a member of such a body of persons.</content></paragraph></subsection><subsection id="ID_1748244148916_014" name="4" temporalId="s2_4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content>A person who contravenes subsection (2) or (3) commits an offence and is liable on conviction to a fine at level 3.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1748244148916_015" name="5" temporalId="s2_5"><num value="5">(5)</num><leadIn>In this section—</leadIn><def name="Secretary"><term>Secretary</term> (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">局長</term>) means the Secretary for Health;</def><def name="TheChineseMedicineHospitalOfHongKong"><term>The Chinese Medicine Hospital of Hong Kong</term> (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">香港中醫醫院</term>) means the hospital that—<paragraph id="ID_1748244149448_016" name="a" temporalId="s2_5_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>is known as “The Chinese Medicine Hospital of Hong Kong” in English and “香港中醫醫院” in Chinese; and</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1748244149448_017" name="b" temporalId="s2_5_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>is situated at 1 Pak Shing Kok Road, Tseung Kwan O, New Territories.</content></paragraph></def></subsection></section><section startPeriod="2025-05-23T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1748244149448_018" name="s3" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Certain enactments amended for covering The Chinese Medicine Hospital of Hong Kong etc.</heading><content>The enactments specified in the <ref>Schedule </ref>are amended as set out in the Schedule.</content></section><schedule startPeriod="2025-05-23" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1748244150635_019" name="sch0" temporalId="sch0"><num value="0">Schedule </num><note role="crossReferences" type="inline